The decision process followed by unsatisfied agents is largely similar to that of defecting satisfied agents, with the  exception that at the outset of the decision process agents will chose to explore a new product, chosen at random from the set of remaining products, with probability Î±.
The selection of a new  product begins by the agent identifying those products from which he or she expects to gain a satisfactory performance on all attributes i.e.
